sql:
SELECT COUNT(*)
FROM performance
WHERE boom_pts > (SELECT AVG(boom_pts) FROM performance);

external_knowledge:
cumulative fantasy points refers to the running total of fantasy points created by each player over time, with the 'top players' being those who have the highest cumulative fantasy points on each game day; 
game day refers to the date of the game;
details of the player include the actual score, projected score, and fantasy points created;
